author: WCAX News
title: Police: Traffic stop led to cocaine bust
text:
ROCKINGHAM, Vt. - Vermont state police say a traffic stop led to a cocaine bust.
Around 9:30 p.m. Monday, police say they stopped Roberto Caraballo, 28, of Springfield, Massachusetts, on Interstate 91 in Rockingham for speeding.
During a search, police say they found a quarter ounce of crack cocaine in Caraballo's underwear.
Caraballo was held on bail.
